<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF7EFF34A7ADFC5DFAB1D823" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF7EFF34A7ADFC5DFEE9DFCD" blockId="231.[189,303,946,972]" box="[189,303,946,972]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF7EFF34A7ADFC5DFEE9DFCD" bold="true" box="[189,303,946,972]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A7ADFC5DFEE9DFCD" bold="true" box="[189,303,946,972]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF7EFF34A7ADFC0CFAB1D823" blockId="231.[188,1399,995,1059]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
This species was originally described in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF7EFF34A41AFC0CFCB1DFFC" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Giupponi &amp; Prendini &amp; Scharff" authorityYear="2021" box="[778,887,995,1021]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A41AFC0CFCB1DFFC" box="[778,887,995,1021]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Charinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is hereby transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF7EFF34A3D4FC0CFACEDFFC" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[1220,1288,995,1021]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Sarax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A3D4FC0CFACEDFFC" box="[1220,1288,995,1021]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Sarax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the phylogenetic analyses of 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF7EFF34A51DFBE7FCCCD822" author="Miranda G. S. &amp; Giupponi A. P. &amp; Scharff N. &amp; Prendini L." box="[525,778,1032,1059]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Miranda" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" refId="ref151478" refString="Miranda G. S., Giupponi A. P., Scharff N. &amp; Prendini L. 2021. Phylogeny and biogeography of the pantropical whip spider family Charinidae (Arachnida: Amblypygi). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / zoolinnean / zlaa 101" title="Phylogeny and biogeography of the pantropical whip spider family Charinidae (Arachnida: Amblypygi)" type="book" year="2021">
<collectingRegion id="C52E6C81FF7EFF34A51DFBE7FDB6D823" box="[525,624,1032,1058]" country="Venezuela" name="Miranda" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Miranda</collectingRegion>
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF7EFF34A567FBE6FD76D823" box="[631,688,1032,1058]" italics="true" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">et al.</emphasis>
(2021)
</bibRefCitation>
. See 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF7EFF34A454FBE7FB78D822" author="Weygoldt P. &amp; Van Damme K." box="[836,1214,1032,1059]" firstAuthor="Weygoldt" journalOrPublisher="Fauna of Arabia" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" pagination="327 - 334" part="20" refId="ref156483" refString="Weygoldt P. &amp; Van Damme K. 2004. A new troglomorphic whip spider of the genus Charinus (Amblypygi: Charinidae) from Socotra Island. Fauna of Arabia 20: 327 - 334." title="A new troglomorphic whip spider of the genus Charinus (Amblypygi: Charinidae) from Socotra Island" type="journal article" year="2004">
Weygoldt &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="C52E6C81FF7EFF34A4C8FBE6FBC0D822" box="[984,1030,1033,1059]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Van</collectingRegion>
Damme (2004)
</bibRefCitation>
for description.
</paragraph>
